    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-27T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-27T19:00:00-05:00" n="287"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/3587: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-27T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 27, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. The first meeting of the Mixed Commission composed of delegates of the
                    opposition and delegates of the three political parties took place this
                    afternoon. I commenced the proceedings with a brief address emphasizing again
                    the salient features of President Roosevelt’s message to the Cuban people<note
                        n="29" xml:id="d287fn29">See telegram No. 49, June 21, 5 p.m., to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba, <ref target="#pg_311">p. 311</ref>.</note> as made
                    public on July 1st. The meeting was significant in that for the first time in 3
                    years constructive discussion between members of the opposition and of the
                    Government’s adherents took place. A distinctly patriotic and satisfactory
                    spirit was shown by both sides and agreement was reached on several important
                    features of the constitutional reform as proposed. The next meeting of this
                    Commission will be held tomorrow and every day subsequently under my
                    chairmanship until a final agreement is reached.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
